abstract: In a speech last month to farmers in Texas, President Donald Trump won applause as he talked up recent U.S. trade agreements. When he tried to boast of his administration's ethanol policy, however, he was met with silence.
snippet: In a speech last month to farmers in Texas, President Donald Trump won applause as he talked up recent U.S. trade agreements. When he tried to boast of his administration's ethanol policy, however, he was met with silence.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — In a speech last month to farmers in Texas, President Donald Trump won applause as he talked up recent U.S. trade agreements. When he tried to boast of his administration's ethanol policy, however, he was met with silence.
headline_main: Iowa's Anger Over Trump's Ethanol Policy Gives Democrats Opening
headline_print_headline: Iowa's Anger Over Trump's Ethanol Policy Gives Democrats Opening

abstract: Two women were arrested in Florida after police opened fire on them for running two security checkpoints near Mar-a-Lago on Friday in a car chase that was unrelated to U.S. President Donald Trump's resort, officials said.
snippet: Two women were arrested in Florida after police opened fire on them for running two security checkpoints near Mar-a-Lago on Friday in a car chase that was unrelated to U.S. President Donald Trump's resort, officials said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two women were arrested in Florida after police opened fire on them for running two security checkpoints near Mar-a-Lago on Friday in a car chase that was unrelated to U.S. President Donald Trump's resort, officials said.
headline_main: Two Women in Custody for Running Checkpoints at Trump's Florida Resort
headline_print_headline: Two Women in Custody for Running Checkpoints at Trump's Florida Resort

abstract: A future U.S.-UK trade agreement must incorporate strong provisions on worker rights, environmental protection, and enforcement to ensure bipartisan support, U.S. House Ways and Means Committee Chairman Richard Neal said on Friday, staking out a claim for Congress to help shape any such accord.
snippet: A future U.S.-UK trade agreement must incorporate strong provisions on worker rights, environmental protection, and enforcement to ensure bipartisan support, U.S. House Ways and Means Committee Chairman Richard Neal said on Friday, staking out a c...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A future U.S.-UK trade agreement must incorporate strong provisions on worker rights, environmental protection, and enforcement to ensure bipartisan support, U.S. House Ways and Means Committee Chairman Richard Neal said on Friday, staking out a claim for Congress to help shape any such accord.
headline_main: U.S.-UK Trade Deal Needs Labor, Climate Protections, Enforcement: U.S. Lawmaker
headline_print_headline: U.S.-UK Trade Deal Needs Labor, Climate Protections, Enforcement: U.S. Lawmaker

abstract: President Donald Trump signed an executive order on Friday aimed at preventing counterfeit products from abroad from being sold to U.S. citizens who shop online using Amazon.com, Walmart.com or other ecommerce websites, the White House said.
snippet: President Donald Trump signed an executive order on Friday aimed at preventing counterfeit products from abroad from being sold to U.S. citizens who shop online using Amazon.com, Walmart.com or other ecommerce websites, the White House said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump signed an executive order on Friday aimed at preventing counterfeit products from abroad from being sold to U.S. citizens who shop online using Amazon.com, Walmart.com or other ecommerce websites, the White House said.
headline_main: Trump Signs Executive Order Aimed at Preventing Sales of Counterfeit Goods From Overseas
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs Executive Order Aimed at Preventing Sales of Counterfeit Goods From Overseas

abstract: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu met with the leader of Sudan on Monday and said they began talks on normalization, a major diplomatic breakthrough with an Arab and African state two days after the Arab League rejected a U.S. Mideast initiative that heavily favors Israel.
snippet: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu met with the leader of Sudan on Monday and said they began talks on normalization, a major diplomatic breakthrough with an Arab and African state two days after the Arab League rejected a U.S. Mideast init...
lead_paragraph: KAMPALA, Uganda — Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu met with the leader of Sudan on Monday and said they began talks on normalization, a major diplomatic breakthrough with an Arab and African state two days after the Arab League rejected a U.S. Mideast initiative that heavily favors Israel.
headline_main: Israeli PM Meets Sudan's Leader, Aims for 'Normalization'
headline_print_headline: Israeli PM Meets Sudan's Leader, Aims for 'Normalization'

abstract: Both sides hinted on Sunday at what could be part of their closing arguments.
snippet: Both sides hinted on Sunday at what could be part of their closing arguments.
lead_paragraph: Both sides hinted on Sunday at what could be part of their closing arguments. Representative Adam B. Schiff, Democrat of California and the lead House impeachment manager, rejected the argument made by Republican senators that Mr. Trump’s political fate should be decided in the 2020 election, stressing that the president has been charged with soliciting foreign interference in that same election.
headline_main: How will each side conclude its arguments?

abstract: Lawmakers will hear up to four hours of closing arguments, divided equally between impeachment managers and the president’s lawyers.
snippet: Lawmakers will hear up to four hours of closing arguments, divided equally between impeachment managers and the president’s lawyers.
lead_paragraph: What we’re expecting to see:The impeachment managers and Mr. Trump’s lawyers are set to deliver their closing arguments.
headline_main: Here’s what to expect on Monday.

abstract: Germany's current account surplus remained the world's largest last year despite trade tensions, the Ifo economic institute will say on Monday, in an estimate likely to renew criticism of Chancellor Angela Merkel's fiscal policies.

lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Germany's current account surplus remained the world's largest last year despite trade tensions, the Ifo economic institute will say on Monday, in an estimate likely to renew criticism of Chancellor Angela Merkel's fiscal policies.

abstract: Better late than never, YouTube is making clear there will be no “birtherism” on its platform during this year's U.S. presidential election. Nevermind that the conspiracy theory around former President Barack Obama's citizenship emerged in 2008 and has not been a widespread issue since he last ran for president in 2012.
